      <li><a href="#impact">Community Impact</a></li>
      <li><a href="#lessons">Lessons Learned</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
  <main>
    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>In May 2018, the Solai Dam in Nakuru County, Kenya, collapsed, leading to 47 deaths and massive displacement of residents. Investigations revealed regulatory failures and environmental negligence.</p>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZaMLeFcAkUs?si=32eBQlEA3WeJjegB" target="_blank" class="button">Watch Video</a>
    </section>
    <section id="charges">
      <h2>Nature of Charges</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manslaughter:</strong> Negligence in dam safety and loss of life.</li>
        <li><strong>Neglect of Duty:</strong> Failure to inspect and monitor the dam.</li>
        <li><strong>Environmental Oversight:</strong> Lack of a proper Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="proceedings">
      <h2>Legal Proceedings</h2>
      <p>The case faced significant delays and ended in dismissal due to the prosecution's inability to present evidence. This highlighted systemic failures in Kenya's legal system.</p>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Eq65QQD9dSk?si=CyshW4vAIk8pWzdV" target="_blank" class="button">Learn More</a>
    </section>
    <section id="impact">
      <h2>Community Impact</h2>
      <p>The collapse devastated families and communities. Survivors faced trauma, and many struggled with rebuilding their lives and securing compensation.</p>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/49rRs3xfA5k?si=BSyRqT3yF95iDWAC" target="_blank" class="button">View Aftermath</a>
    </section>
    <section id="lessons">
      <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
      <p>This tragedy underscores the need for strict environmental regulations, efficient legal processes, and accountability to prevent similar disasters.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
